:10'),('2f30790d-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','ed1b33e8-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','2f303811-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','454cf028-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','In the lesson \'Implement Service Workers, Cache API, and IndexedDB with TypeScript\', what does the provided starter code log to the console?','[\"service worker installed\", \"service worker activated\", \"service worker registering failed\"]',1,'2026-05-16 17:26:10','2026-05-16 17:26:10'),('2f31fa74-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','ed1b33e8-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','2f30eea9-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','454cf028-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','In the lesson \'Design reusable generics, mapped, and conditional types for UI patterns\', what does the starter code log to the console?','[\"mapped types ready\", \"generics ready\", \"types ready\"]',1,'2026-05-16 17:26:10','2026-05-16 17:26:10'),('2f336917-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','ed1b33e8-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','2f332530-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','454cf028-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','In the lesson \'Apply type guards, branded types, and runtime validation for safety\', what does the starter code print to the console?','[\"valid user invalid user\", \"valid user\", \"invalid user\", \"valid user valid user\"]',0,'2026-05-16 17:26:10','2026-05-16 17:26:10'),('2f33d87b-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','ed1b33e8-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','2f3397c4-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','454cf028-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','In the lesson \'Write unit and integration tests for TypeScript web apps with Jest and testing-library\', what does the starter-code log to the console after running its internal assertions?','[\"tests passed\", \"tests failed\", \"all tests passed\", \"2 tests passed\"]',0,'2026-05-16 17:26:10','2026-05-16 17:26:10'),('2f344152-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','ed1b33e8-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','2f340732-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','454cf028-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','In the lesson \"Optimize bundle size and performance with tree-shaking and code splitting\", what is the exact console output of the provided starter code when run without triggering the lazy load?','[\"app initialized light feature executed\", \"app initialized heavy feature executed\", \"app initialized\", \"light feature executed app initialized\"]',0,'2026-05-16 17:26:10','2026-05-16 17:26:10'),('2f34a373-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','ed1b33e8-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','2f346f1d-5133-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','454cf028-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','In the lesson \'Migrate an existing JavaScript web app to TypeScript incrementally and deploy\', what does running the starter code log to the console?','[\"migration ready: start incremental conversion\", \"migration ready start incremental conversion\", \"migration ready - start incremental conversion\", \"Migration ready start incremental conversion\"]',1,'2026-05-16 17:26:10','2026-05-16 17:26:10'),('55da6544-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','What primary responsibilities does Express provide on top of Node\'s HTTP module?','[\"Routing and middleware composition\", \"Automatic database integration\", \"Rendering desktop applications\", \"Replacing Node\'s event loop\"]',0,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55db853b-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','If you have routes \'/users/:id\' and \'/users/me\', which should you register first to ensure \'/users/me\' is matched for the literal path?','[\"Register \'/users/:id\' first\", \"Register \'/users/me\' first\", \"Order does not matter\", \"Use only one of them\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55dc4b16-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','written','Explain why the service layer should be independent of Express request/response objects.','[\"Keeping services independent makes them easier to unit-test, reusable across transports (e.g., scheduled jobs), and less tightly coupled to the HTTP framework, enabling clearer separation of concerns.\"]',0,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55de1793-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','true_false','Middleware registered earlier runs before middleware registered later.','[\"True\", \"False\"]',0,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55de99f9-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','What is the main advantage of a centralized error handler in Express?','[\"It makes the server run faster\", \"It standardizes error responses and logging\", \"It automatically fixes bugs\", \"It replaces middleware\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55df1269-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Which is a reasonable validation for a user password in an API?','[\"Allow empty string passwords\", \"Require a minimum length and character constraints\", \"Store the password as plain text after validation\", \"Skip validation and trust the client\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55dfd57a-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Where should database queries ideally live in a well-structured Express app?','[\"Directly in route definitions\", \"In the service (or repository) layer\", \"Inside middleware only\", \"In the client code\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55e14b3c-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','What does wrapping an async route handler with a helper (asyncHandler) primarily achieve?','[\"Makes the function synchronous\", \"Ensures rejected promises are forwarded to error handlers\", \"Increases performance\", \"Prevents use of await\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55e209f4-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Why is it useful to have both request-level and model-level validation?','[\"Model-level is obsolete if request-level exists\", \"Both increase redundancy but are unnecessary\", \"Request-level prevents bad requests early; model-level enforces invariants at persistence\", \"They are the same and one is sufficient\"]',2,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55e2b340-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','What is a security risk when using JWTs if you store sensitive data in the payload?','[\"JWT payloads are encrypted by default\", \"JWT payloads are readable and can expose sensitive information\", \"JWTs cannot be revoked\", \"JWTs always expire immediately\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55e32ee0-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Which of the following helps prevent cross-site scripting (XSS) issues in API responses?','[\"Sending raw HTML in JSON responses\", \"Setting appropriate Content Security Policy headers and sanitizing inputs\", \"Allowing all origins in CORS\", \"Using only HTTP (not HTTPS)\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55e3b77b-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Which test type should be the fastest and most numerous in your test suite?','[\"End-to-end tests\", \"Integration tests\", \"Unit tests\", \"Manual tests\"]',2,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('55e43689-4fd8-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Which is a recommended practice when creating production Docker images for Node apps?','[\"Include devDependencies in the final image\", \"Use multi-stage builds to minimize final image size\", \"Store secrets in the image environment variables\", \"Run the app as root user\"]',1,'2026-05-15 00:03:19','2026-05-15 00:03:19'),('658c9f6b-4fce-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Which command initializes a new Node.js project and creates package.json?','[\"npm install express\", \"npm init\", \"node server.js\", \"npm start\"]',1,'2026-05-14 22:52:11','2026-05-14 22:52:11'),('658dc582-4fce-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','true_false','Express is a framework built on top of Node.js to make web servers easier to write.','[\"True\", \"False\"]',0,'2026-05-14 22:52:11','2026-05-14 22:52:11'),('658fd1b5-4fce-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','Which method starts the Express server and listens on a port?','[\"app.run()\", \"app.listen()\", \"express.listen()\", \"server.start()\"]',1,'2026-05-14 22:52:11','2026-05-14 22:52:11'),('65907a8f-4fce-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-ba5b-00090ffe0001','multiple_choice','What does app.use(express.json()) do?','[\"Serves static files\", \"Parses incoming JSON request payloads\", \"Encrypts request bodies\", \"Starts the server\"]',1,'2026-05-14 22:52:11','2026-05-14 22:52:11'),('6590fe48-4fce-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','dde5cde4-4fcc-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821',NULL,'454cde6d-4f80-11f1-b